reviews.text: This place is simple and awesome. As in filled with awe.

Won't address what I think about the institution but will talk only about the building, which is absolutely AMAZING. One of the most beautiful architectures in the city and in Israel, with a lot of natural light and a lot of symbols and meaning in how it was built. A gift for any photographer of architecture lover, views on the city and beautiful garden nearby as a bonus (also, worth checking the building from the outside and don't miss the courtyard!).
Free daily tours that are open to the general public take place at 11 a.m. in Hebrew and at 12 noon in English.
Accessibility: accessible parking, entrance to the building, toilets, water stations, voice guidance system, audio assistance system at the reception, directing signage, audio systems in courtrooms.
I believe everyone in Israel's supreme court should watch Lauren Southern's video on why feminism is an antynom for equality. Feminism is a movement for entitlements and supremacy.
They got a illuminati thing on top that aint cool. Flip the (bad) jews in here
Very impressive. Highly recommend the guided tour is about 1 hour long. Free.

Very small museum, cool knowledgeable guides that seem to master a lot of the countrie's historic, traditional and mythological stories. In an hour you can see most part of it. There is a little shop outside of the museum where you can buy some artifacts that are also available elsewhere at lesser price.
I like this place but I would love it if it had enough traditional and local object. I think it doesn't represent enough the national heritage

I loved visiting this museum. I wish I could've taken pictures. Nevertheless, our tour guide, William Dayo, was very well versed in each of the exhibits. It was really nice to have someone with us who gave us in depth information on what we were viewing. It gave us a deeper understanding and appreciation for each of the artifacts.
It was nice. The museum has a lot to offer in cultural history and I was happy to see them opened on a Sunday.

This museum continues the tradition of equating Western African culture and history mainly with masks (sarcasm). It could almost be interchangeable with the museum's in Dakar and Bamako except they both have a second floor dedicated to textiles. 

Granted, the masks are interesting and high quality, but they are completely decontextualized with cryptic captions an little explanation tying anything together.

There is one table showing the evolution of money that was nice. 

It's one of the few times I wished there was a museum gift shop with some books. 

Weirdly they don't allow photography either, as if history should be hidden. 

Avoid the restaurant out back it is way overpriced and there are better maquis around.
Disappointingly small and not focused enough on the migration of the Serbs, interaction with other Slavic / Balkan cultures. On the other hand, super inexpensive (~$4USD
A great collocation of national heritage and costumes of all regions! Recommended for Slavists especially!
This museum was recently renovated. We visited 2 weeks ago and loved it.
Beautiful.different periods of culture,life,.on english too.water,toilet,very important.

This museum has clothes, tools, furniture, and recreations of living spaces of Serbian people from the past. They're still working on exhibits today so it's not fully functional completely right now but there are still many things to see in the upper levels.
The price is much higher than Vietnamese food here (like 3x-4x expensive), yet still acceptable as the food quality is excellent! You will enjoy a happy French dinner here. Recommended!

Food is good whilst price is reasonable.
The time I visited here is for celebrate my boyfriend and I sent email for reservation. However, the owner didn’t confirm me if Bday cake can be prepared even I have sent several emails before I start my trip.....

The food is great and delightful here. Even though it has a higher price than average restaurant here in Danang, but I think it’s worthy to try, and I think I will come back again in the next trip in Danang.
A traditional delicious french restaurant. My wife and I enjoy a romantic dinner here. It is highly recommended.

Good cuisine over priced , quality is good , portions are not consistent with price 
They showed special of the day ! Lobster Bisque which we order ,after few minutes they said it won't be available after 2 hours , for the level price of what they pretend to be ??? 
We pay deliver be careful with over price !

The restaurant is located in Monaco and very easy to find. The moment I entered it, I was fascinated by the atmosphere and decoration. We were a group of three and had reserved a table online. Sadly, one part of the menu did not have an English version, but the friendly waitress explained everything in fluent English (which is not expectable in France!). We ordered the lunch set menu and were very satisfied by the chef‘s creations. The combinations were wonderful abd supported the taste.
I‘d like to note that a reservation is highly recommended, eventhough the process might be a little complicated. I can understand that no-shows are irritating, but having customers depositing their credit card for a cancellation fee of 150€ in case late modification of the booking or no-show is an overreaction in my opinion. I think the restaurant should trust customers for calling in advance, if they no they cannot show up.
I had a great time with my hubby and really like the atmosphere

Utterly disoppinted with the level of service and communication level at the reservations and no one was on the floor to recieve us to lead us to the table.  The person on the phone taking the reservations was highly rude when we arrived at the recieption  and we were asked to remove our blazzers which she confused with a fur over coat. the staff needs a lot of training with soft skills and specially english speaking skills.
I don't understand why everyone is crazy over the sushi here. It tastes like a sushi place at a train station in Japan. Everything else is good though
This place is opens 2 times in week... Thursday and Friday... Went there twice both times was closed... Locals did not considered it as good bar...

Always a beautiful meal here and the steak is always perfectly cooked (medium rare). Lovely service, we have a family meal here for most of the big birthdays. Glad Dumfries still has somewhere like this.
Decent. Food was ok but underwhelming... Dishes ordered were chosen with high expectations but minimal flavour coming through and tough meat let it down. Chips were nice. Well presented too.
Delightful  fresh food. Gorgeous  desserts. Friendly  helpful staff.  A nice place to meet friend's  for a relaxing lunch , no time pressure  to vacate the table.
Superb Monday lunch, three courses and a beer with the wife. Brilliant can't recommend highly enough. Good sized portions and fantastic service.
We were down from Edinburgh we had been recommended this restaurant by friends, it is a hidden gem , lovely food , friendly staff and beautiful surroundings, will definitely be back

One of my favorite Thai restaurants in Berlin. Food is awesome at good prices. Great choice, mostly crowded (because so good), so you should better make a reservation, especially at the evening / weekend
If one loves Thai food, this is the place to go. I recommend the papaya salad

I have such a wonderful experience at the restaurant. The food is really authentic and definitely "zab". If you are craving for Thai food, this is the place to come. I recommend slow-cooked pork noodle and Som Tum, papaya salad.
Spicy Thai food for very good price. Very tasty Tom Kha Gai. This place is bigger than the other Papaya and seem to serve more options. Great deal for a lunch in this area.

I really enjoy my food here. I ordered Pad Thay with garnelen and Ice Tea. It was really good decision! The food was soooo good!
The Rindfleischsuppe is also delicious! 
They accept card ;)

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.

They have a 15 minute, live concert every weekday at noon, where they play different types of music on the bells. Sometimes traditional music, sometimes modern music. You can hear it from all over campus!
Iconic Iowa State clock tower
Iconic Iowa State landmark
Great place to take wedding photos.

The iconic clock/bell tower that's featured in pretty much any photo collection of Iowa State University.  There's always a small musical performance at noon as well as the quarter hour chimes during normal business hours.  The recent construction of a short wall on Union Dr. (just south of the campanile) has become a really popular spot for people to take photos while visiting ISU.

Went in by myself & the lady who I presume is the owner was very kind & genuine. the food itself (I got the bee bim bop) was AMAZING & the price was very reasonable. highly recommend. nice little "hole in the wall" restaurant

I’m not sure how this place received 4+ stars. The egg rolls had no taste and the dish I had was bland. My sister’s food wasn’t all that great either. She ordered a burrito and they brought her a quesadilla that had way too much cheese(never thought that was possible). The waitress was nice but the food left so much to be desired.

This place is truly a hidden gem in Columbia! Just discovered it the other day after being here for 5 years and I’m so glad I did. Food was awesome and our waiter was so sweet and made sure we had an awesome experience. I came in with my service cat (hairless), and she even brought out a plate of boiled fish for him!! Which he LOVED! She not only made sure I was happy but made sure my little one was happy too!! I love this place!!
Blue Cactus is so good. It's a straight forward, no frills place with EXCELLENT food. It's not a fast food place, so expect a short wait, but the food is definitely worth it.
Very good food and a variety of choices. I had the beef over rice, my daughter had Thai curry.
